  "prompt": "Do candles spoil?",
  "response": "Candles generally do not spoil, but they can degrade over time, especially if not stored properly. Here are some factors that can affect the quality and longevity of candles:\n\n1. **Wax Type:** Different types of wax have varying lifespans. For example, paraffin wax candles tend to last longer than natural wax candles made from soy or beeswax.\n\n2. **Scent:** Scented candles can lose their fragrance intensity over time, especially if exposed to air and light.\n\n3. **Storage Conditions:** Proper storage is crucial for maintaining a candle's quality. Keep candles in a cool, dark place, away from direct sunlight and extreme temperatures. Exposure to heat can cause the wax to soften and lose its shape, while cold can make the wax brittle.\n\n4. **Humidity:** High humidity can affect the wax and wick, potentially causing the candle to burn unevenly or not light properly.\n\n5. **Dust and Debris:** Dust and debris can settle on the surface of the candle and wick, affecting its ability to burn cleanly.\n\nBy storing candles properly, you can ensure they last for a long time without significant degradation.",
